<headline>Special Weather Statement issued February 22 at 7:55AM EST  by NWS Detroit</headline>
<description>...WINTER WEATHER ADVISORY REMAINS IN EFFECT...
WEATHER...
* Temperatures will hover around or just below the freezing mark
this morning as precipitation increases coverage and intensity
between 800 AM and 1000 AM.
* A greater frequency of freezing rain occurrence is expected
near the Saginaw Bay shoreline from Port Austin to Bay City and
then inland across Bay and Midland counties.
IMPACTS...
* Light icing will lead to hazardous conditions on untreated
roads and walking surfaces.
&amp;&amp;
PRECAUTIONARY/PREPAREDNESS ACTIONS...
* Motorists are urged to use caution and account for hazardous
driving conditions by slowing down and allowing extra time.
* Prepare, plan and stay informed. Visit http://go.usa.gov/c7kkP</description>
